sentences.english: Jenna was always happy and bubbly, a lovely person.
sentences.chinese: 珍娜總是很高興，生氣勃勃的，是一個可愛的人。

sentences.english: His fresh enterprise is full of life and has a bright future.
sentences.chinese: 他新興的事業生氣勃勃，前途光明。

sentences.english: Vibrant small- and medium-sized enterprises are key engines of economic growth.
sentences.chinese: 生氣勃勃的中小型企業是經濟增長的主要動力。

sentences.english: Not only are the user groups and conferences lively.
sentences.chinese: 用戶組和相關會議都開展得生氣勃勃。

sentences.english: His new [fresh] enterprise is full of life and has a bright future.
sentences.chinese: 他新興的事業生氣勃勃，前途光明。

sentences.english: And it was an exuberant, exuberant time.
sentences.chinese: 那真是一段生氣勃勃的時光。

sentences.english: With green number distribution, appear lively.
sentences.chinese: 用數分配綠意盎然，顯得生氣勃勃。

sentences.english: A good book is the precious life-blood of master spirit.
sentences.chinese: 好書是一個生氣勃勃者的活力來源。

sentences.english: Her original vigorous pride of youth had sickened.
sentences.chinese: 她原先那種生氣勃勃的青春自豪感已經萎謝。

sentences.english: The spirited young organization has more team spirit.
sentences.chinese: 這個生氣勃勃少年組織很有團隊精神。

sentences.english: The dynamic comedy duo will have you splitting your sides with laughter.
sentences.chinese: 這一對生氣勃勃的喜劇搭檔能讓你笑破肚皮。

sentences.english: The green base with white flowers and web decoration creates a sense of pureness and freshness.
sentences.chinese: 與白花和網裝飾的綠色基地創造清和生氣勃勃感覺。

sentences.english: She was vibrant with health and enthusiasm.
What a quiet but lively scene. Lambs frisked about in the pastures.
sentences.chinese: 跳去，這是一幅多麼恬靜而又生氣勃勃的景象啊。
生氣勃勃卻不太誠實的移民。

sentences.english: A good book is the precious life-blood of a master-spirit.
sentences.chinese: 好書是一個生氣勃勃的人活力的來源。
